1
00:01:55,540 --> 00:01:56,239
Coming.

2
00:02:01,739 --> 00:02:02,540
Professor.

3
00:02:02,859 --> 00:02:03,640
Xiao Cai.

4
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:05,659
You scared me to death yesterday.

5
00:02:05,859 --> 00:02:07,060
If I hadn't learned...

6
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:08,780
some simple first aid back in the day.

7
00:02:08,780 --> 00:02:10,900
You call that simple first aid?

8
00:02:10,979 --> 00:02:11,939
Good grief.

9
00:02:11,939 --> 00:02:14,300
It was like a hex wrench and pliers.

10
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,340
Pinching my philtrum...

11
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:17,139
nearly pried my front teeth off.

12
00:02:17,139 --> 00:02:17,939
Sorry.

13
00:02:18,020 --> 00:02:20,219
But if I didn't use force, you wouldn't wake up.

14
00:02:20,219 --> 00:02:21,039
That's true.

15
00:02:21,180 --> 00:02:21,740
But wait.

16
00:02:22,060 --> 00:02:23,539
The stock went up.

17
00:02:23,539 --> 00:02:25,020
What were you shouting about?

18
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:27,659
I was really shocked too.

19
00:02:28,099 --> 00:02:28,819
In the morning...

20
00:02:29,219 --> 00:02:29,939
we just bought the stock...

21
00:02:29,939 --> 00:02:31,979
and by afternoon it was up ten percent!

22
00:02:32,139 --> 00:02:33,219
How could I not shout?

23
00:02:33,219 --> 00:02:35,099
You're incredibly lucky.

24
00:02:35,099 --> 00:02:35,659
You...

25
00:02:35,659 --> 00:02:37,020
shouldn't be buying stocks.

26
00:02:37,020 --> 00:02:38,340
You should buy lottery tickets.

27
00:02:39,580 --> 00:02:40,099
Here.

28
00:02:40,099 --> 00:02:41,699
This is the one thousand yuan profit.

29
00:02:41,780 --> 00:02:42,860
You take it first.

30
00:02:43,060 --> 00:02:44,180
Later I'll have Xiao Qian...

31
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:46,099
bring the principal back over.

32
00:02:46,219 --> 00:02:47,099
Great. We'll just...

33
00:02:47,099 --> 00:02:48,120
stop right here.

34
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:49,020
That's great.

35
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:49,979
What's so great about it?

36
00:02:50,699 --> 00:02:52,300
Happiness has just begun.

37
00:02:52,699 --> 00:02:54,180
How can we stop now?

38
00:02:54,259 --> 00:02:54,860
No way.

39
00:02:54,860 --> 00:02:55,659
Absolutely not.

40
00:02:56,259 --> 00:02:57,539
Do me a favor...

41
00:02:57,539 --> 00:02:58,780
keep helping me trade.

42
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:00,180
Keep trading?

43
00:03:00,379 --> 00:03:01,180
I wouldn't dare.

44
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:02,219
If someone dies...

45
00:03:02,219 --> 00:03:03,500
I can't take the responsibility.

46
00:03:05,219 --> 00:03:06,500
Wasn't that just because...

47
00:03:06,699 --> 00:03:08,659
it was my first time fainting?

48
00:03:08,659 --> 00:03:09,659
I promise.

49
00:03:09,819 --> 00:03:11,819
From now on, let the stock soar like crazy.

50
00:03:11,819 --> 00:03:12,740
Let it skyrocket.

51
00:03:12,740 --> 00:03:14,639
No matter how high, I won't faint.

52
00:03:15,020 --> 00:03:15,939
How high it goes...

53
00:03:16,340 --> 00:03:17,620
is that up to me?

54
00:03:18,979 --> 00:03:20,060
You don't have the say.

55
00:03:20,060 --> 00:03:21,060
Who calls the shots?

56
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:21,759
Honestly.

57
00:03:22,939 --> 00:03:24,020
Professor, my brother.

58
00:03:24,139 --> 00:03:26,060
I've figured it all out.

59
00:03:26,379 --> 00:03:27,539
This one thousand yuan...

60
00:03:27,539 --> 00:03:28,319
Five hundred yuan...

61
00:03:28,419 --> 00:03:29,099
is for you.

62
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:30,979
And this five hundred is for my grandson.

63
00:03:31,219 --> 00:03:32,620
Why does that sound so awkward?

64
00:03:32,780 --> 00:03:33,539
I don't want this money.

65
00:03:33,539 --> 00:03:34,419
Not a single cent.

66
00:03:34,419 --> 00:03:35,620
Give it all to your grandson.

67
00:03:35,979 --> 00:03:37,379
That sounds awkward to me too.

68
00:03:37,780 --> 00:03:38,500
Take it.

69
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:39,259
I don't want it.

70
00:03:39,539 --> 00:03:40,819
I really... I can't take a cent.

71
00:03:40,819 --> 00:03:41,159
Take it.

72
00:03:41,159 --> 00:03:41,979
I say... honestly.

73
00:03:41,979 --> 00:03:42,960
I really don't want it.

74
00:03:43,259 --> 00:03:44,020
You think it's too little, right?

75
00:03:44,020 --> 00:03:44,560
Fine.

76
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:45,659
Then this...

77
00:03:46,060 --> 00:03:47,060
This one thousand yuan...

78
00:03:47,419 --> 00:03:48,340
You take it all.

79
00:03:48,340 --> 00:03:49,060
That's not what I meant. We'll earn more.

80
00:03:49,060 --> 00:03:50,139
I really don't want it. We'll earn more.

81
00:03:50,139 --> 00:03:51,180
Please don't do this.

82
00:03:51,180 --> 00:03:52,099
Men and women shouldn't touch.

83
00:03:52,099 --> 00:03:52,740
Let's not do this, okay?

84
00:03:52,740 --> 00:03:53,139
No touching.

85
00:03:53,139 --> 00:03:54,539
Why are you holding on so tight?

86
00:03:54,539 --> 00:03:56,139
No, this... I can't take your...

87
00:03:56,139 --> 00:03:56,900
You two...

88
00:03:58,020 --> 00:03:59,340
You two... I didn't see anything.

89
00:03:59,340 --> 00:04:00,379
I didn't see a thing.

90
00:04:00,379 --> 00:04:01,240
I'm just looking.

91
00:04:01,419 --> 00:04:02,060
Don't.

92
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:03,460
Don't say you didn't see anything!

93
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:04,259
Ms. Liu.

94
00:04:04,460 --> 00:04:05,580
Look closely.

95
00:04:06,139 --> 00:04:07,180
What we're doing here...

96
00:04:07,340 --> 00:04:08,580
what are we doing?

97
00:04:08,620 --> 00:04:09,120
This...

98
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:09,939
We're...

99
00:04:10,099 --> 00:04:11,120
We're exercising, right?

100
00:04:11,219 --> 00:04:11,680
We're...

101
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:12,280
practicing...

102
00:04:12,479 --> 00:04:13,219
Push Hands.

103
00:04:13,219 --> 00:04:13,919
Right.

104
00:04:14,099 --> 00:04:15,060
Push Hands.

105
00:04:15,060 --> 00:04:15,819
Just like this.

106
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:17,100
Push.

107
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:17,740
Right.

108
00:04:17,740 --> 00:04:18,899
Pushing back and forth.

109
00:04:24,459 --> 00:04:25,379
Mutton hotpot?

110
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:26,899
That works.

111
00:04:27,019 --> 00:04:28,060
Everyone's here.

112
00:04:28,980 --> 00:04:29,980
Have some candy.

113
00:04:32,379 --> 00:04:34,420
Where did the sun rise from today?

114
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:36,540
Ms. Cai has become so generous.

115
00:04:36,579 --> 00:04:37,899
What are you saying?

116
00:04:38,819 --> 00:04:41,060
I'm not generous every day.

117
00:04:41,060 --> 00:04:41,699
No.

118
00:04:41,779 --> 00:04:43,899
I can't be generous every day.

119
00:04:43,899 --> 00:04:44,699
I...

120
00:04:44,699 --> 00:04:45,540
Just eat your candy.

121
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:48,540
Ms. Cai isn't just giving out candy.

122
00:04:48,660 --> 00:04:50,339
She bought new clothes too.

123
00:04:50,579 --> 00:04:52,420
She looks forty years younger.

124
00:04:52,620 --> 00:04:53,500
You noticed.

125
00:04:54,259 --> 00:04:55,839
I bought this at the mall on sale.

126
00:04:56,019 --> 00:04:57,339
Thirty yuan a piece.

127
00:04:57,339 --> 00:04:57,899
Is it worth it?

128
00:04:57,899 --> 00:04:58,980
Worth it. Definitely.

129
00:04:58,980 --> 00:05:01,060
That's why Old Cai is so good at managing money.

130
00:05:01,819 --> 00:05:03,800
Buying up all these clearance items at once.

131
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:04,459
Shoo.

132
00:05:04,779 --> 00:05:06,160
These aren't clearance items.

133
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,819
This schoolbag is for my grandson.

134
00:05:07,819 --> 00:05:08,779
It cost over a hundred.

135
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,540
This pencil case was over seventy.

136
00:05:10,699 --> 00:05:11,779
This tracksuit...

137
00:05:11,939 --> 00:05:13,899
...was two hundred even after twenty percent off.

138
00:05:14,459 --> 00:05:15,300
Ms. Cai.

139
00:05:15,740 --> 00:05:16,920
For a child...

140
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,100
...to use such expensive things...

141
00:05:18,220 --> 00:05:19,199
...isn't good for cultivating...

142
00:05:19,199 --> 00:05:20,779
...a style of hard work and plain living.

143
00:05:21,060 --> 00:05:21,939
Boss Li.

144
00:05:23,459 --> 00:05:26,899
His grandma has lived hard her whole life.

145
00:05:27,019 --> 00:05:28,459
Lived plainly for most of it.

146
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:30,540
Now for my grandson's generation...

147
00:05:30,660 --> 00:05:31,459
...still plain?

148
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:32,740
It's time for a change.

149
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:33,899
You guys chat.

150
00:05:34,139 --> 00:05:35,100
Old Fan, come here.

151
00:05:35,379 --> 00:05:36,420
Candy Ms. Cai bought.

152
00:05:37,220 --> 00:05:38,019
Hold on.

153
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,819
How can Professor Fan eat candy?

154
00:05:40,899 --> 00:05:42,899
I bought chocolate especially for you.

155
00:05:43,220 --> 00:05:44,899
Silky as satin.

156
00:05:45,139 --> 00:05:45,980
Why?

157
00:05:46,060 --> 00:05:47,740
We can only eat fruit candy...

158
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:48,600
...but Professor Fan...

159
00:05:48,779 --> 00:05:50,540
...gets to eat "satin"?

160
00:05:50,740 --> 00:05:52,459
Is eating satin appropriate?

161
00:05:52,540 --> 00:05:53,699
He's eating choc...

162
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:56,160
Right, why does he get to eat chocolate?

163
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:58,060
Of course he can eat chocolate.

164
00:05:58,100 --> 00:05:59,620
Because Professor Fan...

165
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:02,379
...he didn't do anything.

166
00:06:03,139 --> 00:06:03,939
Here.

167
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:05,019
Eat up.

168
00:06:05,019 --> 00:06:06,699
Wait, if he didn't do anything...

169
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:07,579
...he gets chocolate?

170
00:06:07,579 --> 00:06:09,259
We didn't do anything either.

171
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:10,579
Can we compare?

172
00:06:10,660 --> 00:06:12,139
That is chocolate.

173
00:06:12,220 --> 00:06:13,620
It has special meaning.

174
00:06:13,779 --> 00:06:14,540
Ms. Liu.

175
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:15,779
What's special about it?

176
00:06:15,779 --> 00:06:16,860
Let's all eat together.

177
00:06:16,860 --> 00:06:17,579
No.

178
00:06:17,639 --> 00:06:18,579
We won't eat it.

179
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:21,100
If you won't eat it, I will.

180
00:06:35,819 --> 00:06:36,620
Old Fan

181
00:06:37,620 --> 00:06:39,339
Why are you up so early today?

182
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:40,899
That's right

183
00:06:41,660 --> 00:06:42,600
Starting today,

184
00:06:42,699 --> 00:06:44,279
I'm going to start exercising too

185
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:46,339
You see,

186
00:06:46,660 --> 00:06:48,300
under my influence and leadership,

187
00:06:48,779 --> 00:06:49,980
Professor Fan, who usually stays up all night

188
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:51,300
and never gets up in the morning,

189
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:53,360
has finally gotten up early to exercise

190
00:06:54,939 --> 00:06:55,740
Tell me,

191
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:57,860
how should you thank me?

192
00:06:58,139 --> 00:06:59,579
Thank you for what?

193
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,019
Look at you

194
00:07:01,459 --> 00:07:02,420
You're always like this

195
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:03,459
Always the same

196
00:07:03,819 --> 00:07:04,800
Only I,

197
00:07:05,019 --> 00:07:05,839
being the bigger person,

198
00:07:05,939 --> 00:07:06,920
won't hold it against you

199
00:07:07,540 --> 00:07:08,339
How about this?

200
00:07:08,339 --> 00:07:09,699
I'll take you on as a disciple

201
00:07:10,019 --> 00:07:11,220
We can skip the initiation ceremony

202
00:07:11,420 --> 00:07:12,980
You don't even have to pay tuition

203
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,660
How about I teach you Yang-style Tai Chi first?

204
00:07:16,180 --> 00:07:17,100
Yang-style?

205
00:07:17,420 --> 00:07:19,379
My mother was also called Yang Shi when she was young

206
00:07:19,379 --> 00:07:20,819
I should be the one teaching you this style

207
00:07:20,819 --> 00:07:22,180
What do you mean you teach me?

208
00:07:22,259 --> 00:07:23,060
Honestly

209
00:07:23,379 --> 00:07:24,079
Where are you going?

210
00:07:24,259 --> 00:07:25,899
It's a secret. I'm not telling you

211
00:07:25,899 --> 00:07:26,819
A secret, huh?

212
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:28,379
Didn't we agree

213
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:30,019
to meet at the waterside pavilion?

214
00:07:31,779 --> 00:07:32,560
Little Cai is here

215
00:07:32,699 --> 00:07:33,259
Professor

216
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:33,980
Boss Li

217
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:34,740
You're both here

218
00:07:35,540 --> 00:07:37,079
Fried dough sticks, milk, eggs

219
00:07:38,339 --> 00:07:39,779
Piping hot. Just bought from the cafeteria

220
00:07:39,779 --> 00:07:40,980
Still hot

221
00:07:41,019 --> 00:07:42,339
Boss Li, you haven't had breakfast yet, right?

222
00:07:42,339 --> 00:07:43,060
Not yet

223
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:45,220
You should hurry and go eat

224
00:07:45,220 --> 00:07:46,879
Otherwise, the fried dough sticks will get soggy

225
00:07:47,139 --> 00:07:47,980
These fried dough sticks are just right

226
00:07:47,980 --> 00:07:48,259
I...

227
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:50,779
I actually wanted to buy a portion for you too

228
00:07:50,779 --> 00:07:51,860
But then I thought,

229
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:53,819
you always have that...

230
00:07:53,819 --> 00:07:55,699
finish exercising before eating breakfast

231
00:07:55,699 --> 00:07:56,339
Right? Yes

232
00:07:56,339 --> 00:07:57,779
That is your good lifestyle habit

233
00:07:57,779 --> 00:07:58,579
I shouldn't break it

234
00:07:58,579 --> 00:07:59,220
Don't you agree?

235
00:07:59,220 --> 00:07:59,980
That is true

236
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:01,220
Why haven't you gone

237
00:08:01,220 --> 00:08:03,100
to practice that Tai Chi yet?

238
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:04,000
I was just about to go

239
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:04,779
Chop-chop

240
00:08:04,779 --> 00:08:05,600
Hurry up

241
00:08:05,660 --> 00:08:07,160
Look at the time!

242
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:07,879
Hurry up

243
00:08:09,779 --> 00:08:11,699
I know what the secret is

244
00:08:16,779 --> 00:08:18,500
What do you know?

245
00:08:18,579 --> 00:08:19,839
Come over and eat.

246
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:22,300
While it's hot.

247
00:08:23,339 --> 00:08:24,300
Look at you.

248
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:26,620
You won't take a commission.

249
00:08:27,060 --> 00:08:29,019
You won't let me make your bed.

250
00:08:29,420 --> 00:08:31,500
I have no way to repay you.

251
00:08:31,779 --> 00:08:33,139
So I thought, might as well...

252
00:08:33,740 --> 00:08:34,899
Every morning,

253
00:08:34,899 --> 00:08:36,179
I'll buy you breakfast.

254
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:38,059
Fried dough sticks.

255
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:39,460
Bread.

256
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:40,700
Eggs, milk.

257
00:08:40,779 --> 00:08:41,940
Guaranteed variety.

258
00:08:41,940 --> 00:08:42,940
Whatever you like to eat,

259
00:08:42,940 --> 00:08:44,039
I will buy for you.

260
00:08:44,259 --> 00:08:45,580
What I like to eat...

261
00:08:45,580 --> 00:08:46,759
Is whatever's bad for my health.

262
00:08:46,980 --> 00:08:47,659
Forget it.

263
00:08:47,659 --> 00:08:48,779
Don't buy things for me anymore.

264
00:08:48,779 --> 00:08:50,159
I have to go practice my Tai Chi sword.

265
00:08:50,159 --> 00:08:50,820
Don't.

266
00:08:51,179 --> 00:08:53,100
Don't go practice Tai Chi sword.

267
00:08:53,179 --> 00:08:54,500
Come, sit down.

268
00:08:55,419 --> 00:08:56,899
You haven't told me yet.

269
00:08:57,019 --> 00:08:59,700
Which stock are we buying today?

270
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,539
Good heavens.

271
00:09:01,539 --> 00:09:02,580
Comrade Cai Xiaoying.

272
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:03,620
I'll make a call right now.

273
00:09:03,620 --> 00:09:05,379
To get your money back and return it to you.

274
00:09:05,779 --> 00:09:06,659
You, all day long...

275
00:09:06,659 --> 00:09:08,779
Chasing and pestering me like this.

276
00:09:08,779 --> 00:09:10,299
I really can't take it anymore.

277
00:09:10,620 --> 00:09:11,419
Don't.

278
00:09:11,460 --> 00:09:13,059
Don't be angry.

279
00:09:13,059 --> 00:09:14,740
Great Professor Fan.

280
00:09:14,940 --> 00:09:17,240
Isn't it the money urging me on?

281
00:09:18,580 --> 00:09:19,539
How about this.

282
00:09:19,539 --> 00:09:22,179
You just teach me how to trade stocks.

283
00:09:22,179 --> 00:09:22,940
Okay?

284
00:09:23,059 --> 00:09:24,299
Isn't there that...

285
00:09:24,620 --> 00:09:26,080
Was it...

286
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,620
Confucius or Laozi...

287
00:09:27,620 --> 00:09:29,179
Or Sunzi who said that...

288
00:09:29,179 --> 00:09:30,179
That famous quote.

289
00:09:30,659 --> 00:09:31,779
If you want to eat fish,

290
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:34,100
You have to know how to swim, right?

291
00:09:34,139 --> 00:09:35,740
You want to go into the river to catch fish?

292
00:09:36,179 --> 00:09:39,980
It's "Give a man a fish; teach a man to fish."

293
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:40,940
It means...

294
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:42,259
Giving you a fish...

295
00:09:42,340 --> 00:09:42,899
Is not as good as...

296
00:09:42,899 --> 00:09:43,620
Giving me two fish.

297
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:44,159
Right.

298
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:45,460
What do you mean "right"?

299
00:09:45,460 --> 00:09:46,740
What two fish?

300
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:47,659
It means...

301
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:49,500
It's better to teach you how to fish.

302
00:09:49,740 --> 00:09:51,299
That's exactly what I meant.

303
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:52,940
So hurry up and teach me to fish.

304
00:09:52,940 --> 00:09:54,179
Why would I learn to fish?

305
00:09:54,179 --> 00:09:56,620
Hurry up and teach me to trade stocks.

306
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:57,940
Look, how about this.

307
00:09:57,940 --> 00:10:00,460
You take me to that stock factory.

308
00:10:00,460 --> 00:10:01,659
Let's go look around.

309
00:10:01,860 --> 00:10:02,659
Take a look.

310
00:10:03,259 --> 00:10:03,779
Learn a bit.

311
00:10:03,980 --> 00:10:05,220
Then I'll know how to trade stocks.

312
00:10:05,220 --> 00:10:07,299
And I won't have to bother you every day.

313
00:10:08,779 --> 00:10:10,019
That is true.

314
00:10:11,580 --> 00:10:12,500
I've agreed.

315
00:10:12,779 --> 00:10:13,740
One last time.

316
00:10:18,539 --> 00:10:19,840
Our Professor Fan,

317
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:22,120
is living the good life recently.

318
00:10:23,019 --> 00:10:25,100
He has personal service for food and water.

319
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:27,100
Making his bed, folding his quilt.

320
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:29,139
A fitness partner for push-hands.

321
00:10:29,740 --> 00:10:31,220
Plus dating.

322
00:10:32,059 --> 00:10:34,039
What nonsense are you talking about?

323
00:10:35,820 --> 00:10:36,940
He's just being shy.

324
00:10:36,940 --> 00:10:37,659
Look.

325
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:39,179
Ms. Liu.

326
00:10:39,379 --> 00:10:41,100
You have no idea.

327
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:43,299
When an old house catches fire,

328
00:10:43,299 --> 00:10:44,539
there's no saving it.

329
00:10:44,779 --> 00:10:46,139
Isn't that what I told you?

330
00:10:46,139 --> 00:10:48,259
It's from Qian Zhongshu's novel, Fortress Besieged.

331
00:10:49,860 --> 00:10:51,059
So you admit it then?

332
00:10:51,379 --> 00:10:52,980
This is a great thing!

333
00:10:53,299 --> 00:10:55,259
Looks like we'll be switching rooms soon.

334
00:10:55,259 --> 00:10:56,220
There's no rush.

335
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:57,779
What do you mean?

336
00:10:57,860 --> 00:10:59,220
Who's switching rooms with whom?

337
00:10:59,779 --> 00:11:00,620
Professor Fan.

338
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:02,139
I'm ready.

339
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:03,340
Let's go.

340
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:04,940
Do I even need to say who?

341
00:11:05,379 --> 00:11:06,179
Cai Xiaoying.

342
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:08,860
Professor Fan has been waiting for you for ages.

343
00:11:09,059 --> 00:11:11,019
Where are you two going today?

344
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:11,980
What do you mean "you two"?

345
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:13,139
I'm not going anywhere.

346
00:11:14,899 --> 00:11:16,220
Didn't we agree on this earlier?

347
00:11:16,220 --> 00:11:17,379
You can't go back on your word.

348
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:20,379
It was all settled, right?

349
00:11:20,980 --> 00:11:22,820
We can't be fickle and heartless.

350
00:11:22,899 --> 00:11:24,539
And act like a scumbag.

351
00:11:25,139 --> 00:11:25,940
A scumbag.

352
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:27,139
Right, a scumbag.

353
00:11:28,059 --> 00:11:29,659
Who's a scumbag? Who?

354
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:30,860
Let me tell you.

355
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,340
I'm taking Little Cai to see...

356
00:11:32,340 --> 00:11:33,039
See a movie.

357
00:11:33,399 --> 00:11:34,600
Professor Fan said he'd take me to see...

358
00:11:34,980 --> 00:11:35,799
That's not it at all.

359
00:11:36,379 --> 00:11:37,779
I'm not going to see a movie.

360
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:38,899
Professor Fan.

361
00:11:39,220 --> 00:11:40,019
Whether you see a movie or not...

362
00:11:40,019 --> 00:11:41,779
...what does that have to do with us?

363
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:43,539
Is there any need to explain to us?

364
00:11:43,779 --> 00:11:45,000
Right, Ms. Liu?

365
00:11:45,220 --> 00:11:45,899
That's right.

366
00:11:46,139 --> 00:11:47,740
Anyway, since you've made plans...

367
00:11:47,740 --> 00:11:49,019
You should get going.

368
00:11:49,059 --> 00:11:50,659
Or the movie will start without you.

369
00:11:50,659 --> 00:11:52,139
It really has nothing to do with a movie.

370
00:11:52,139 --> 00:11:53,620
I really have to explain this to you.

371
00:11:53,620 --> 00:11:54,940
No need to explain anymore.

372
00:11:55,019 --> 00:11:56,259
Any later and the stock mark...

373
00:11:56,620 --> 00:11:58,580
...the story film will start.

374
00:11:58,899 --> 00:12:00,740
I'll explain to you later, Ms. Liu.

375
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:01,919
Honestly.

376
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:04,659
Things have gone this far...

377
00:12:04,659 --> 00:12:05,580
...and he still wants to explain.

378
00:12:05,580 --> 00:12:06,700
Explain what?

379
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:08,179
What is there to be afraid of?

380
00:12:08,539 --> 00:12:09,700
Don't we seniors...

381
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:11,220
...have emotional lives too?

382
00:12:11,740 --> 00:12:12,700
Are you saying...

383
00:12:13,740 --> 00:12:15,220
Professor Fan and Auntie Cai...

384
00:12:16,059 --> 00:12:17,179
No way.

385
00:12:17,539 --> 00:12:18,659
Why not?

386
00:12:19,220 --> 00:12:20,659
A single man and a single woman.

387
00:12:21,139 --> 00:12:22,460
A talented man and a beauty...

388
00:12:22,980 --> 00:12:24,179
...though she's not exactly a beauty...

389
00:12:24,659 --> 00:12:26,100
...but there are no obstacles.

390
00:12:27,059 --> 00:12:28,139
What I mean is...

391
00:12:28,379 --> 00:12:30,779
A retired professor and a laid-off worker.

392
00:12:31,580 --> 00:12:33,419
Isn't the gap a bit too wide?

393
00:12:33,419 --> 00:12:35,179
What's wrong with a wide gap?

394
00:12:35,899 --> 00:12:37,460
I was a poor boy back in the day.

395
00:12:37,899 --> 00:12:39,500
I fell in love with a capitalist's daughter.

396
00:12:40,259 --> 00:12:42,379
Didn't I still manage to win her over?

397
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:44,500
That was during extraordinary times.

398
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:47,100
There are plenty of examples from ancient times too.

399
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:48,139
For example...

400
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:50,620
Dong Yong and the Seventh Fairy.

401
00:12:51,220 --> 00:12:52,539
A poor boy...

402
00:12:52,539 --> 00:12:53,659
...and a fairy.

403
00:12:54,379 --> 00:12:55,659
One plows the fields...

404
00:12:55,659 --> 00:12:56,899
...the other weaves cloth.

405
00:12:57,059 --> 00:12:58,139
It didn't affect anything.

406
00:12:58,500 --> 00:12:59,299
And then there's...

407
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:00,860
Zhuge Liang and Huang Yueying.

408
00:13:01,580 --> 00:13:02,500
One was a viral heartthrob...

409
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:03,779
...and the other was famously plain.

410
00:13:03,940 --> 00:13:05,820
Didn't they still make it work?

411
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:07,419
And also...

412
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:08,940
Xu Xian and Lady White Snake.

413
00:13:09,179 --> 00:13:10,500
Zhu Bajie and Gao Cuilan.

414
00:13:11,059 --> 00:13:12,779
Tuxingsun and Deng Chanyu.

415
00:13:13,779 --> 00:13:15,139
Chen Shimei and Qin Xianglian.

416
00:13:15,460 --> 00:13:16,820
They all had big gaps between them.

417
00:13:16,980 --> 00:13:18,500
But the examples you just mentioned...

418
00:13:19,179 --> 00:13:21,220
...didn't seem to end very well.

419
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:24,059
That's an after-sales issue.

420
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:25,620
It has nothing to do with us.

421
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:27,299
As long as there's a spark...

422
00:13:27,659 --> 00:13:29,299
...anything can happen.

423
00:13:29,620 --> 00:13:31,100
Look at Professor Fan and Little Cai.

424
00:13:31,179 --> 00:13:32,899
So we should all support them.

425
00:13:32,899 --> 00:13:33,740
Help them out.

426
00:13:34,100 --> 00:13:35,460
How are we supposed to help?

427
00:13:35,460 --> 00:13:36,639
In our volunteer handbook...

428
00:13:36,639 --> 00:13:37,720
...there's no service for this.

429
00:13:38,899 --> 00:13:40,179
Everyone, let's take action.

430
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:41,740
Notify everyone.

431
00:13:41,940 --> 00:13:43,460
Create every opportunity for them.

432
00:13:43,460 --> 00:13:44,899
Let them be together as much as possible.

433
00:13:45,139 --> 00:13:46,000
Boss Li.

434
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:49,539
Why are you so enthusiastic about this?

435
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:50,440
Isn't this just me...

436
00:13:52,220 --> 00:13:53,100
...finding joy in helping others?

437
00:13:57,340 --> 00:13:58,139
It's pure.

438
00:13:58,139 --> 00:13:59,240
Right, pure.

439
00:14:01,460 --> 00:14:02,120
Xiao Cai

440
00:14:02,379 --> 00:14:03,019
You're back.

441
00:14:03,539 --> 00:14:05,100
How was the movie?

442
00:14:05,220 --> 00:14:06,460
We really didn't go to the movies.

443
00:14:06,460 --> 00:14:07,220
Professor Fan.

444
00:14:07,460 --> 00:14:08,419
We're done eating.

445
00:14:08,419 --> 00:14:09,419
We'll make room for you.

446
00:14:09,419 --> 00:14:10,500
You two take your time.

447
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:11,179
Okay.

448
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:11,820
Let's go.

449
00:14:11,899 --> 00:14:12,799
Don't go.

450
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:14,399
All of you...

451
00:14:14,399 --> 00:14:15,080
Don't leave, everyone.

452
00:14:15,399 --> 00:14:15,639
Wait...

453
00:14:15,639 --> 00:14:16,080
We're done eating.

454
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:16,799
We've finished our meal.

455
00:14:16,799 --> 00:14:18,100
Don't go, everyone.

456
00:14:18,759 --> 00:14:19,179
Let them go.

457
00:14:19,179 --> 00:14:20,259
Just let them go.

458
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:21,240
Professor Fan.

459
00:14:22,179 --> 00:14:23,500
About the market K-lines...

460
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,080
You still have to explain it to me.

461
00:14:25,179 --> 00:14:26,240
Don't explain!

462
00:14:27,059 --> 00:14:28,720
I can't even explain myself clearly now.

463
00:14:28,899 --> 00:14:30,460
What are you afraid of?

464
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:31,980
Worst case, tonight back in the room...

465
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:33,980
I'll explain it directly to Ms. Liu.

466
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:34,700
On your behalf.

467
00:14:35,820 --> 00:14:37,340
Mom, there you are.

468
00:14:37,340 --> 00:14:38,820
I've been looking for you all afternoon.

469
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:41,299
What are you doing here, kid?

470
00:14:41,299 --> 00:14:42,460
Have you eaten yet?

471
00:14:42,460 --> 00:14:43,179
I have.

472
00:14:43,259 --> 00:14:44,000
Listen...

473
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:45,980
Did that little fox...

474
00:14:45,980 --> 00:14:46,960
...kick you out again?

475
00:14:47,179 --> 00:14:48,940
Mom, look at you, as soon as you open your mouth...

476
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:51,460
My wife's name is Hu Xiaoli.

477
00:14:51,460 --> 00:14:52,659
I'm talking about Hu Xiaoli.

478
00:14:52,659 --> 00:14:54,340
You just said "little fox."

479
00:14:54,340 --> 00:14:55,039
Fine.

480
00:14:55,299 --> 00:14:55,919
What's the matter?

481
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:56,779
The thing is...

482
00:14:57,539 --> 00:14:58,820
Just this afternoon...

483
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:00,220
Our little fox...

484
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,179
Hu Xiaoli.

485
00:15:02,179 --> 00:15:03,799
It's all your fault, I'm confused.

486
00:15:03,940 --> 00:15:04,899
My wife...

487
00:15:04,899 --> 00:15:06,779
...was washing clothes for our Doudou.

488
00:15:06,779 --> 00:15:07,740
Guess what?

489
00:15:07,899 --> 00:15:09,340
From inside the kid's pocket...

490
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:10,820
...she found five hundred yuan.

491
00:15:11,179 --> 00:15:12,620
She asked him where the money came from.

492
00:15:12,740 --> 00:15:14,379
He insisted you gave it to him.

493
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:15,519
At such a young age...

494
00:15:15,519 --> 00:15:17,059
...he's already learned to lie.

495
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:17,980
I did give it to him.

496
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:19,419
You gave it?

497
00:15:20,139 --> 00:15:21,740
How is that possible, Mom?

498
00:15:21,779 --> 00:15:23,259
How much rent do you collect a month?

499
00:15:23,259 --> 00:15:24,500
Don't I know it?

500
00:15:24,620 --> 00:15:27,419
After paying the odds and ends for this retirement community...

501
00:15:27,419 --> 00:15:28,580
...there's barely anything left.

502
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:29,820
I really did give it to him.

503
00:15:30,179 --> 00:15:31,259
Mom, you...

504
00:15:31,580 --> 00:15:33,539
...can't protect the calf like this.

505
00:15:33,779 --> 00:15:35,019
You darn kid.

506
00:15:35,179 --> 00:15:36,980
Who calls their own son a calf?

507
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:38,779
Let me tell you.

508
00:15:39,220 --> 00:15:41,100
Mom's income is limited.

509
00:15:41,220 --> 00:15:43,080
But this money, I have.

510
00:15:43,820 --> 00:15:45,059
If you don't believe me...

511
00:15:45,139 --> 00:15:46,220
...ask Professor Fan.

512
00:15:47,399 --> 00:15:48,460
Ask me?

513
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:49,899
Right.

514
00:15:50,419 --> 00:15:51,620
Mom, who is this?

515
00:15:52,059 --> 00:15:53,259
Let me introduce you.

516
00:15:53,899 --> 00:15:54,700
This gentleman...

517
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:56,059
...is our Evergreen Residence's...

518
00:15:56,059 --> 00:15:58,200
...most respected Professor Fan.

519
00:15:58,580 --> 00:15:59,980
Call him Uncle Fan.

520
00:16:00,620 --> 00:16:01,580
Hello, Uncle Fan.

521
00:16:01,580 --> 00:16:02,259
Hello.

522
00:16:02,899 --> 00:16:04,539
That five hundred yuan for Doudou...

523
00:16:04,580 --> 00:16:05,899
...was given to me by him.

524
00:16:06,940 --> 00:16:07,779
I gave it?

525
00:16:09,419 --> 00:16:10,220
That's right

526
00:16:10,659 --> 00:16:11,620
It amounts to me giving it

527
00:16:11,620 --> 00:16:12,419
You gave it

528
00:16:12,419 --> 00:16:14,059
I really have to thank you for this

529
00:16:14,980 --> 00:16:15,940
That's not right

530
00:16:15,940 --> 00:16:18,179
Why would you give my mom money for no reason?

531
00:16:18,179 --> 00:16:18,940
I am

532
00:16:18,980 --> 00:16:19,659
Is it

533
00:16:19,659 --> 00:16:20,159
No

534
00:16:20,379 --> 00:16:21,539
It wasn't me, right?

535
00:16:21,539 --> 00:16:22,779
What is it... it's just me

536
00:16:22,779 --> 00:16:23,820
It... the thing is

537
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:24,740
Exactly

538
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:26,259
Uncle Fan

539
00:16:26,259 --> 00:16:27,740
You think Mom looks cute

540
00:16:27,860 --> 00:16:28,659
No

541
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:30,620
You think Doudou looks cute

542
00:16:30,620 --> 00:16:31,460
And then?

543
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,659
You asked Doudou to give Mom pocket money

544
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:34,340
No

545
00:16:34,860 --> 00:16:36,860
You asked Mom to give Doudou pocket money

546
00:16:36,860 --> 00:16:38,120
Now you understand, right?

547
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:39,460
I'm even more confused

548
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:40,980
I'd better sort this out myself

549
00:16:41,379 --> 00:16:42,299
It's like this

550
00:16:42,379 --> 00:16:44,740
You think my mom looks cute

551
00:16:44,740 --> 00:16:46,299
So you gave her five hundred yuan

552
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:47,940
That's inappropriate

553
00:16:48,419 --> 00:16:49,139
It's like this

554
00:16:49,139 --> 00:16:49,980
It was you

555
00:16:49,980 --> 00:16:51,940
You think our Doudou looks cute

556
00:16:51,940 --> 00:16:53,659
So you gave my mom five hundred yuan

557
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:55,700
Anyway, I...

558
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:56,740
My brain is a bit slow

559
00:16:56,740 --> 00:16:59,340
I feel something is wrong here

560
00:16:59,419 --> 00:17:00,220
What's wrong?

561
00:17:00,220 --> 00:17:01,220
What could be wrong?

562
00:17:01,220 --> 00:17:02,379
Why are you so troublesome, child?

563
00:17:02,379 --> 00:17:04,119
Knowing I gave the money is enough, isn't it?

564
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:04,480
Hurry up

565
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:05,339
Go home

566
00:17:05,460 --> 00:17:06,700
Tell that little vixen

567
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:07,799
Don't wrongly accuse my grandson

568
00:17:08,539 --> 00:17:09,539
You said it again

569
00:17:09,539 --> 00:17:10,420
Uncle Fan, did you hear that?

570
00:17:10,420 --> 00:17:11,380
She said it again

571
00:17:11,980 --> 00:17:12,720
What did I say?

572
00:17:12,859 --> 00:17:13,440
You said

573
00:17:13,519 --> 00:17:14,319
Little vixen

574
00:17:14,319 --> 00:17:14,859
Go

575
00:17:18,619 --> 00:17:19,500
Little Cai

576
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:21,819
Isn't it tiring hiding things from everyone?

577
00:17:22,019 --> 00:17:23,819
Just tell the truth and be done with it

578
00:17:24,220 --> 00:17:26,059
I really can't tell

579
